                                                                                                          \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/samsung-galaxy-watch-fe-arm-2.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/samsung-galaxy-watch-fe-arm-2.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/samsung-galaxy-watch-fe-arm-2.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/samsung-galaxy-watch-fe-arm-2.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                \u003cimg width=\"3000\" height=\"1688\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"The Samsung Galaxy Watch FE\u0026#39;s always-on display. \" data-img-url=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/samsung-galaxy-watch-fe-arm-2.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/samsung-galaxy-watch-fe-arm-2.jpg\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\t\t\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\n\n        \n                    \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan data-field=\"label\"\u003eRelated\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n                \n        \n        \n        \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"what-39-s-great-about-the-samsung-galaxy-watch-fe\"\u003e\n                        What\u0026#39;s great about the Samsung Galaxy Watch FE?\n               \u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n    \n\n\n\n                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                \n    \n\n\u003cp\u003eSamsung\u0026#39;s come a long way since its first smartwatch, and now produces some of the best wearables for Android that you can buy in 2025. But if you\u0026#39;re looking for something that\u0026#39;s affordable yet feature-packed, the brand has you covered there as well, with its Galaxy Watch FE. \u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eThe Galaxy Watch FE on sale is the 40mm version, which packs a 1.2-inch AMOLED screen and is powered by Samsung\u0026#39;s Exynos W920 chip. The watch also features 1.5GB of RAM and also 16GB of internal storage. For the most part, the watch is pretty zippy for daily use, and the software is pretty good thanks to Wear OS. \u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eSamsung makes its own customizations for the software experience, but having access to popular apps via the Google Play Store helps maximize the Galaxy Watch FE in most situations. As you might expect with a modern smartwatch, you get health and fitness tracking, along with stress and sleep quality readings as well. \u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eFor the most part, there\u0026#39;s not a lot to complain about with this watch. You get ample years of software support going forward, which will keep things modern and fresh, and it\u0026#39;s just $109. If you\u0026#39;ve been thinking about buying your first smartwatch, or just wanted to update your current one for cheap, this is the way to go. \u003c/p\u003e    \u003c/div\u003e\n    \n                \n        \n        \n\n\n        \n\n\n\n\n\n                \n    \u003c/article\u003e\n\n    \n            \n        \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
